<description>The version of Splunk installed on the remote host is prior to tested version. It is, therefore, affected by a vulnerability as referenced in the SVD-2025-0301 advisory.

  - In Splunk Enterprise versions below 9.3.3, 9.2.5, and 9.1.8, and Splunk Cloud Platform versions below     9.3.2408.104, 9.2.2406.108, 9.2.2403.114, and 9.1.2312.208, a low-privileged user that does not hold the     admin or power Splunk roles could perform a Remote Code Execution (RCE) through a file upload to the     $SPLUNK_HOME/var/run/splunk/apptemp directory due to missing authorization checks. (CVE-2025-20229)

Note that Nessus has not tested for this issue but has instead relied only on the application&apos;s self-reported version number.</description>
