<ReportItem port="68" svc_name="bootpc?" protocol="udp" severity="0" pluginID="14272" pluginName="Netstat Portscanner (SSH)" pluginFamily="Port scanners">
<agent>unix</agent>
<description>Nessus was able to run &apos;netstat&apos; on the remote host to enumerate the open ports. If &apos;netstat&apos; is not available, the plugin will attempt to use &apos;ss&apos;.

See the section &apos;plugins options&apos; about configuring this plugin.

Note: This plugin runs on Windows using netstat.exe if the target is localhost (scanner scanning itself) or a Windows host authenticated via SSH with the ability to run netstat.exe.</description>
